values: hey guys i dont know if anyone even reads this anymore i kinda forgot about livejournal... but i guess i'll just say that college is amazing? providence college is the best place on earth pretty much, for me at least! if anyone is thinking about looking or coming here just im me or email me or something, really... i have absolutely not one complaint. it's the best place imaginable. no joke. i hope everyone else is happy where they are :)

hey guys.. i'm waiting to go out so i decided to update and waste some time.. life has been pretty good, busy as always. i went to providence last saturday and loved it more than ever. i'm so so excited to go. i seriously loved everything about it..i ran into a few people i know who might go there also so i'm really excited :-) i just hope i like it as much as i think i do, next year.. and that i don't get a wierdo roommate. every day i can't believe that we're graduating and everyone's leaving. i'm so sad, especially about erin probably going to tampa. i hope you read this loser!! i'm going to florida w/ er on monday till thursday. we're going to look at tampa (grr) and then to ft. myers to stay with her aunt. frank is going the same time as us so hopefully we'll hang out :-) last saturday we all went to long beach to drink.. not a good idea. we miss you john! it's gunna be a long two weeks without ya. after our fun ended we still had an awesome time just hanging out with everyone.. on wednesday we all went to lido during the day. it was so awesome almost our whole grade was there and not in school. at first it was kinda cloudy but then it got really nice & i got burnt for the first time this year haha so exciting. ummm what else. oo still can't wait for prom, i'm so happy everything worked out..it's gunna be awesome<3 i'm getting a new digital on sunday hopefully so then i'll be able to take pictures again..it's been way too long. sorry for the randomness of this entry. i hope everyone has an awesome break and the weather's not terrible up here. oh last thing, ap stats is the worst class ever and if anyone reads this who might take it next year.. dont!!



..there's just something about his smile

janet get ready for an entry just like those you described ;-)

i love this weather!
and everything else lately.
senior year really is amazing. everyone is coming back together and friends and i love it. i'm finally coming to realize who are my true friends and appreciating them so much more than ever before.<3

friday night started with us preing at erin's with her grandpa upstairs. the guys came a few at a time until everyone was there & we got so loud playing never ever and telling the funniest stories ever that gpa realized how many people were actually there, so we left and went to annemarie's. thank you so much for this weekend! it was so much fun. she had us all over two nights in a row. lots of other people were there, it was so awesome being with everyone. especially you, and sarah!! times ten<3
on saturday i went out to lunch with the girls to chili's then to anne's for a little. so much fun being with you guys, as always.
at night melissa, tina, liz, michaela & i went to erica's sweet 16. it was kinda weird being the oldest  but we had so much fun. we even got a candle.. the 16th!! she's so cute<3 we left a little early & i went back to annemarie's again. everyone was there again, and i could go on for a while with inside jokes but janet would really kill me. so i'll end now haha

i can't wait for prom!! it's gunna be soo much fun

but most of all, i hate that i don't hate you..
 not even a little bit, not even at all

it's my dad's birthday today. it's so weird that we're getting older.. but even more weird that our parents who we think are already old, are getting even older. but yeah anyway i bought him a polo shirt. i never know what to get my parents so whateverr.

i'm definitely going to providence. i'm SO excited. i realllly can't wait to go away. i love everyone so much, but i've been waiting for this for so long. does anyone know anyone else who's going there? hmm i cant wait

i know high school is all about growing up and changing. but it's so sad how some people drift and change so much. once we used to think we could never live without each other.. then the next second you're barely saying hi to each other. the saying "best friends forever" is so annoying because it's so not true. ugh i just wish everyone could be friends and normal and nothing had to change at all. i know that's unrealistic. i have my little picture in my mind of everyone coming back from college and being friends again..but who's to say that will actually happen. grr so many memories and everything we've been all been through together. that's just life i guess.

sorry for the randomness.. i'm trying to kill time

oh sorry one more thing. ap stats should die. seriously. wtf. it's third quarter. i'm a senior. i do not care about anything anymore. especially stats!! ugh i wanna drop it so bad but my mom would never let me, and "colleges will withdraw your acceptances." ughhh

on a lighter note... <3

two hour delays are the best.. we still have to go to school but you dont do anything in any classes bc they're so short, except i had to take a euro test which was really gay. laur erin sarah and i went to panera for lunch. we didnt have that much time but it was really fun..  after school erin and i went to best buy and wal mart because we had absolutely nothingg to do and she didnt have to babysit.. then we went to the gym with melissa & corey. we were all excited for kickboxing but the instructor girl couldnt make it because of the roads which sucked but oh welll. this weekend should be really good.. i can't waittt  hopefully something like last :-)

pointless point but i felt like updating
<3

hey guys.. i havent updated in a long time so i guess it's time i do.

 i'll start w/ february break- liz and i took the train down to baltimore on thursday. we almost missed the amtrack and were running through penn station w/ our huge vera bradley bags and uggs and northfaces and looked like real snobs not knowing what we were doing haha with everyone laughing at us of course..it was funny tho. we took a cab to loyola where robbie threw a surprise bday party for liz in his dorm. it was really cute. we ate wings & bagels from home and watched oc and played beirut then went out to a bar in baltimore. it was so much fun, until i drank too much and got really sick the next day. when i felt better robbie took me and liz on a tour of loyola and i absolutely loved it and now i really want to go there. if i get in :-/. i really really hope i do. and i really hope i go with danielle!! that would be so awesome.. later that night my dad picked me up & we went down to my aunt's house an hour away from loyola. the next day i woke up really sick so i couldn't visit matt or my cousin. i was sick for the whole week it sucked a lot. by friday i felt better so i went to the city w/ annie and lauren. we went to this pub like place for lunch then i met up with kathy and shannon and a few of their friends and went up to carmel for the night. we visited danielle then went to justin's and george's the next day. it was so much fun. i was so happy to see them. i miss you guys so much. :-(. my cousin came home with me and spent the day & went out to dinner at orchid. at night i went to jimmy's with anne & lauren. then work the next day. that was my vacation. it sucked being sick but wasn't terrible.

 this weekend was by far the best since summer probably. friday night was the senior dance. it was soo much fun. i think almost every single person there was drunk it was so funny. the skits were funny and some were cute but i thought they took up way too much time. by the time they were over, the dance was over. it kinda stunk. i won an ipod shuffle!! courtesy of mrs. russo, thanks nicole! then saturday i went prom dress shopping w/ anne and erin and got extremely depressed because i can not fit into anything. i have the most demented body in the world and i hate it so much. i have noo clue what i'm going to do. but w/e. then we went to erin's to pre. kevin picked us + lauren up to go to dan spieler's. everyone from our school was there, all grades. it was awesome until assholes decided to punch holes in the wall so we had to leave. everyone went from there to katie jordan's which was really fun too, until the same thing happened again.. we have some realll winners in our grade. then we went to taco bell w/ a bunch of people then finally home late. today i slept really late then went to work. i hate working but i love being there. it's so much fun & i love everyone who i work with.

where am i going to college? i have noo clue. i got into mt. st. mary's, scranton, and catholic so far. i'd go to catholic if i didnt get into providence or loyola.. but i dont want to go to the others. so i'm just gunna wait. i can't believe that we're actually leaving, and so soon. i'm really excited but after this weekend i realized how sad it's gunna be leaving everyone.

..prom. ive already complained about my inability to fit into anything. im gunna go to the gym like everyday (yea right) so maybe i'll be able to find something.  but luckily i kinda know who i'm gunna go with which is a plus. i know we'll have a good time like always but i just reallly want to be with my friends. and i really want that to work out. i hope we can all be together.

i have lots of pictures from friday but my digital is broken and i need a new one. anyone have any suggestions? i'm gunna get a new one soon but i dont know what kind.
also.. this is really random, but does anyone have an extra TI-83 i can buy off of someone or something? i'm kinda desperate. ap stats is the death of me. and greg daly borrowed mine and  gave me his which is broken w/out a cover.

everyone has pictures of this weekend up on webshots, check em out.
thanks guys for an amazing much needed weekend<3
ahh i hate being sick. especially during vacation. it ruins everythinggg

last night tina anne and i went to the game at rvc.. it was soo much fun, the fans were like crazy and people almost got in a fight but we have the most awesome cutest assistant principal ever haha so it didnt happen. it was an adventure going home but soo much fun love you tons<3
didnt go to school today.. tina and will picked me up after 4th & brought will back to school then went to panera with terry and brian. soo good as always.
now i'm off to the train station w/ liz to go to loyola. i'll miss you guys!! dont have too much fun without me :-/ haha
<33

panera = <3
boys = </3

i got into scranton. so did tina and brian. yay. i dunno if id go there but at least it's an option.

seriously. wtf. i dont get you! this has been going on for sooo long and it just doesnt make sense and every day i get more and more confused. dont you love the ones that keep you hanging on forever then eventually you get to a point where you go wait why am i even doing this. it's realllly fun. i love boys so much.

liz and i are taking the train down to loyola on thursday to stay w/ robbie.. im really excited. then i'm going to visit matt at mt st mary's. i cant wait to see him. my dad is convinced that im going there, eventho im definitely not.  i might visit my cousin at catholic but im not sure yet.

and prom? yeahhh definitely not having a date for that.

sorry for this totally weird random entry. oh well.

sorry this one's long so don't read it if you wanna get bored.

i dont know why but i'm in such a good mood. i can't even remember the last time i was actually really happy. i dont have a reason to be happy either. i practically failed my euro and stats midterms. i never pay attention in stats and i can't find my glasses so i cant even see the board if i wanted to. i know im a dork. but yeah, so today after school i went to bistro w/ melissa and tina anne and pete came to meet us there. all because i was hungry. it was fun then tina anne and i got our nails done. anne made friends with seventh graders. the guy who did tina's nails was gay with the other nail guy and told me not to have mine done by this girl but i had to anyway so they came out bad. then this girl who had no eyebrows and a fake everything on her body told me to have them fixed but i wouldnt because i was scared so it became this huge thing and the guys were like dont ever go to her but the girl wouldnt fix them for me. so my nails are just messed up but oh well. then i went to the gym with melissa and erin met us a little later for kickboxing. it was so tiring but so much fun. so now i'm here. my mom's really sick. she hasnt been to work since last thursday. i think she has the flu or something like it but it stinks bc i hate seeing her like that. i miss ali. and sarah. so much.  i had so much fun with anne and tina today. i love them a lot.

Wait for the boy who pursues you, the one who will make an ordinary moment seem magical, the kind of boy who brings out the best in you and makes you want to be a better person. Wait for the boy who will be your best friend, who will drop everything to be with you at any time of the day no matter what. Wait for the boy who makes you smile, like no other boy can. Wait for the boy who wants to show you off to the world when you are in sweats and have no make-up on, but appreciates it when you get all dolled up for him. Most of all wait for the boy who will put you at the center of his universe because obviously, he's at the center of yours.

i know everyone has probably seen this a million times but i love it. andd im still waiting. sigh. 
<3
